==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isatin
<hw>I"sa*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Isatis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An orange-red
crystalline substance, <chform>C8H5NO2</chform>, obtained by the
oxidation of indigo blue. It is also produced from certain derivatives
of benzoic acid, and is one important source of artificial indigo.</def>
<altsp>[Written also, less properly, <asp>isatine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isatis</ent>⟦br⟧
